SATIRE here in milder vigour shine
courtly Fashion quit her thin pretence
which erst in kindred darkness lay
veils his hallowed fires , And white-robed Chastity with tears retires

Saps the foundation of a sinking state : When giant-vice and irreligion rise , On mountained falsehoods to invade the skies : Then warmer numbers glow through SATIRE'S page , And all her smiles are darkened into rage : On eagle-wing she gains Parnassus' height , Not lofty EPIC soars a nobler flight : Then keener indignation fires her eye ; Then flash her lightnings , and her thunders fly ; Wide and more wide her flaming bolts are hurled , Till all her wrath involves the guilty world
